cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the behavior of overparametrized neural networks during training. It may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it specifically focuses on neural networks. Additionally, the paper mentions matrix factorization models, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. Finally, the analysis of the models and the empirical demonstrations suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
